.TH MESH-PREVIEW 1 "2026-07-20" "3dlib" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
mesh-preview \- render STL/STEP/mesh files to PNG thumbnails
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B mesh-preview
.I INPUT
.RI [ OUTPUT.png ]
.RB [ \-\-size
.IR N ]
.RB [ \-\-backend
.IR auto|trimesh|simple|freecad ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Generate a PNG preview of a 3D mesh or CAD file for catalog thumbnails.
.P
Uses a dedicated Python venv
.RB ( /usr/local/3dlib/venv-mesh )
with
.B pyglet
1.x because system
.B trimesh
cannot call
.B save_image
with
.B pyglet
2.
.P
.B STEP/STP
files are tessellated with FreeCAD when available, then rendered as a mesh.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-size N
Output size in pixels (default 512).
.TP
.B \-\-backend NAME
.BR auto ,
.BR trimesh
(shaded),
.BR simple
(edge preview, no OpenGL), or
.BR freecad .
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
mesh-preview model.stl /tmp/model.png
mesh-preview part.step /tmp/part.png --size 768
mesh-preview model.stl --backend simple
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR 3dlib (1),
.BR freecad (1).
.SH FILES
.I /usr/local/3dlib/bin/mesh-preview
.br
.I /usr/local/3dlib/venv-mesh/
.SH AUTHOR
Part of the 3dlib project.
